2) gu<207>a (quality); 3)karma (action); 4) s<193>m<193>nya (generality); ç
5) vi·e<218>a (particularity); 6)samav<193>ya (relation of inherence), ç
and 7) abh<193>va (non-existence).
These may now be considered one byone.
<MS>DRAVYA<D> is a substance in which a gu<207>a (quality) and karma ç
(action) can exist. It is the substratum for both.
There are nine kinds of dravyas: the four elements (earth, water, ç
light and air, respectively called p<216>thv<200>, jala, tejas and ç
v<193>yu); <193>k<193>·a (ether); k<193>la (time); dik (space); <193>tman ç
(soul) and manas (mind). All these are eternal.
The four elements exist in the form of param<193><207>us (atoms) before ç
