°k<193>·a, k<193>la, dik and <193>tman are all- pervading whereas ç
manas is a<207>u (atomic) in size.
The Vai·e<218>ika system accepts two kinds of souls: the j<200>v<193>tmans ç
and Param<193>tman (also known as ®·vara or Mahe·vara). The former ç
ones are infinite in number whereas Param<193>tman, the Supreme Soul ç
or God, is only one.
<MS>GUØA<D> or quality is always dependent on dravya or substance ç
for its existence and manifestation. It belongs to a dravya but never ç
to another gu<207>a.
The Vai·e<218>ika system enumerates the gu<207>as as 24. Some of them ç
are: the five qualities of the five sense-organs, pari-m<193><207>a ç
(magnitude), sa<221>yoga (conjunction), buddhi (cognition), sukha ç
